Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Meanwhile saute garlic, chili flakes and anchovies in olive oil for 1-2 minutes or until garlic is slightly yellow in color. Add the tomatoes, olives and capers, bring to a simmer. Season the sauce with salt. Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain pasta and toss with the sauce in a large mixing bowl. Stir in parsley and Romano cheese (optional) before serving.